	dprr:hasNoteText "Author of the Lex Didia sumptuaria, which was applied to Italy as a whole, and made guests as well host liable under the law (Macrob. Sat. 3.17.6, 18 years after the Lex Fannia of 161; cf. Plin. NH 10.139)." .
